Ad Text:
Location: Sydney, Melbourne or Brisbane
Employment type: Permanent
Hours: Full-time (38 hours per week)


St Vincent's Health Australia is a national leader in compassionate, innovative healthcare. Our Virtual & Home division (SVVH) is transforming how care is delivered, using digital innovation and home-based models to create a more connected and equitable health system.

As the Business Analyst, you will support the design, development and optimisation of digital health and service delivery initiatives.

You will work closely with clinical, operational, technical and executive stakeholders to analyse demand, translate complex data into actionable insights, and support scalable, sustainable models of care.

You will play a critical part in enabling data-driven decision-making, supporting digital health innovation, and improving patient outcomes through insight-led service design.

Key Responsibilities

Elicit, analyse and document business and user requirements for digital health initiatives.
Analyse operational, clinical and financial data to identify trends, gaps and opportunities.
Develop dashboards, reports and insights to support decision-making and performance monitoring.
Research population demand, demographics, geography and funding impacts.
Map and improve workflows and processes to enhance efficiency and patient experience.
Support innovation through AI, automation and digital health solutions.
Facilitate workshops, interviews and user journey mapping sessions.
Maintain high-quality documentation including business cases, requirements and process maps.
Support governance, reporting, risk management and benefits realisation activities.


About You
Essential

Demonstrated experience as a Business Analyst (healthcare, digital health or service design preferred).
Strong analytical, problem-solving and data interpretation skills.
Experience in requirements gathering, process mapping and stakeholder engagement.
Proficiency in data visualisation and reporting tools (e.g. Power BI, Tableau).
Excellent communication, facilitation and documentation skills.
Ability to work in agile, cross-functional teams.

Desirable

Experience in virtual care, aged care or health service delivery.
Familiarity with human-centred design and co-design approaches.
Understanding of healthcare funding, regulation and digital health standards.
Experience in not-for-profit or mission-led organisations.


Qualifications

Tertiary qualifications in business, marketing, health administration or a related field.


Why St Vincent's?
Care for each other -as well as the people we serve - underpins everything we do at St Vincent's. Guided by our values of compassion, excellence, integrity and justice, we promote a culture of diversity and inclusion and empower our people to learn, grow and innovate.

We strive to ensure all our people feel supported, valued and safe every day they come to work with us.

When you join the St Vincent's family, you will have access to:

Growth & development: Access ongoing learning, professional development and industry-leading educational partnerships across NSW, VIC and QLD.
Salary sacrifice: As a not-for-profit provider, we offer generous salary packaging - enabling part of your salary to be taken home tax-free, including access to a meal-entitlement card.
Discounts, health and wellbeing: Access a range of employee perks including discounted gym memberships and our free 24/7 staff counselling and wellbeing service.
Workplace giving: Opportunities to engage in volunteering and community programs, including paid volunteering leave and workplace giving initiatives.

This is your opportunity
Shape the future of virtual care in Australia -designing solutions that enable people to live well, with dignity, connection and choice.

Ready to Apply?
If you're driven by purpose, excited by digital care innovation and motivated to build something extraordinary, we'd love to hear from you.

Apply today and help us deliver care that is compassionate, connected, and life changing. Please submit your current CV along with a cover letter.

We will be assessing applications as they are received and may close the advert earlier than the listed closing date.

Because you're like us, you believe in our vision that every person, whoever and wherever they are, is served with excellent and compassionate care, by a better and fairer health and aged care system. Better for all our employees and volunteers, who work tirelessly to provide the highest levels of care and quality of life for our patients and clients. And better support for the local communities we play a vital role in and continue to support.

Pre-Employment Checks
Your employment is conditional upon the completion of all role-required pre-employment checks, including relevant immunisations.

Equal Opportunity
We celebrate diversity & inclusion and are committed to equal employment opportunity for everyone. This affirmative action allows a specific position within St Vincent's to be available exclusively to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander individuals.

About NCVER

The National Centre for Vocational Education Research Ltd (NCVER) is Australia's leading provider of vocational education and training (VET) research and statistics.

We collect, manage, and analyse national VET data and translate it into trusted insights that support better decisions across government, industry, training providers and the broader community.

Working at NCVER means your work has real impact, shaping the evidence base that supports skills, jobs and economic growth across Australia.

About the role

We are looking for an experienced leader to head AskNCVER, NCVER's tailored data and insights service.

In this role, you will lead a multidisciplinary team delivering advisory, analytics, research, and evaluation services that help stakeholders answer complex questions, strengthen decision-making and extend the impact of NCVER's data.

You will balance strategic leadership with hands-on delivery oversight, ensuring projects are high quality, delivered to scope and schedule, and meet customer expectations. You will also play a key role in building strong relationships across the VET sector, government and industry, and in shaping how NCVER continues to evolve its insights and service offerings.

This is a great opportunity for someone who enjoys leading people, building trusted partnerships, and turning data into meaningful outcomes.

A full position description is available on the careers page of our portal at https://www.ncver.edu.au/about-ncver/careers/current-vacancies.

What you will be doing

In this role, you will:

Lead the delivery of AskNCVER's tailored advisory, analytics and evaluation services for internal and external stakeholders.

Oversee a portfolio of complex projects, ensuring quality, timeliness and value for customers.

Build strong, trusted relationships with stakeholders across government, industry and the VET community.

Support the development of service offerings that strengthen NCVER's impact and reputation.

Ensure a strong focus on analytical rigor, continuous improvement and customer experience.

Lead, coach, and develop a multidisciplinary team of data analysts, researchers and information services professionals.

Contribute to the growth of NCVER's core and commercial service streams.

What you will bring

We are looking for someone who can combine strategic thinking with strong delivery discipline, and a customer focused mindset.

Proven experience managing complex data analytics, research, evaluation or data advisory projects end-to-end.

Strong leadership capability, including experience coaching and developing high-performing teams.

Commercial acumen and experience delivering services in a customer-focused environment.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to influence senior stakeholders.

Relevant qualifications and/or experience in data analytics, research, evaluation, information services or related disciplines.

Knowledge of the VET sector (highly regarded)

Why join NCVER

At NCVER you will be part of a respected national organisation delivering work that matters.

We offer:

Ongoing full-time role based in Adelaide (candidates in Sydney, Melbourne, or Canberra may be considered with regular travel to Adelaide required).

Hybrid working arrangements

Gifted leave over the Christmas shutdown period

A competitive salary package commensurate with skills and experience

How to apply

If you are ready to lead the future of NCVER's tailored data and insights service that make a difference nationally, we would love to hear from you.

Please submit:

A cover letter (maximum two pages) outlining your suitability

Your resume

Applications close at 5pm on Friday 13 February, 2026.

NCVER is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome applications from people of all backgrounds, including Aboriginal, Torres Strait Islander, and First Nations people.

Company Description

With roots dating back to 1913, ALDI is proud to make a real difference to people across the world by offering top quality products for low prices. ALDI first entered the Australian grocery market in 2001 and has since grown to have almost 600 stores and 8 distribution centres in 5 states.

If you’ve ever shopped at ALDI you know we are not your average supermarket.  We’re also not your average employer. ALDI is a place where you’ll find good people, good purpose and great opportunities. So, you can work with a great team, feel great for making a real difference for everyday Australians and enjoy a rewarding career.

It’s that simple. ALDI Good Different.

Job Description

Join a highly impactful team as a Strategy Analyst (Storytelling) in the Financial Planning and Analysis (FP&A) department of ALDI Stores, based in Minchinbury. This is a 12-month contract opportunity.

This role sits at the intersection of strategy, finance, retail insight, and visual storytelling. The core job is turning complex commercial analysis into clear, structured, visually appealing narratives that are executive ready. You will have the opportunity to leave a lasting imprint on the business and influence our success.

What does the role involve?   

Develop polished, board-ready presentations and documents, featuring executive briefing notes, structured logic, and visually impactful layouts.
Translate complex datasets from multiple sources, financial models, and analyses into actionable insights, risks and opportunities to executive leaders.
Design process maps, frameworks, timelines, decision trees, and conceptual diagrams to visualise information clearly.
Apply consulting best practice frameworks using problem statements, hypothesis-led thinking, evaluation of options, implications, and recommendations to optimise commercial outcomes.
Collaborate closely with finance, strategy, and operational stakeholders to provide financial support on business strategy and ensure messaging is tailored and effective for CFO, CEO, and Board-level communications.

And the best part? Every single day at ALDI, you'll know you're making a difference, supporting our mission to help everyday Australians live richer lives for less.

Qualifications
Demonstrated experience within a commercial finance, consulting, business analysis environment or similar highly regarded.
Background in Big 4, strategy consulting, internal strategy, or PMO highly regarded.
Proven demonstrated experience of financial planning and analysis.
Proven organisational skills, attention to detail and ability to work under pressure (independently without supervision and in a team environment).
Strong interpersonal and relationship building skills with the ability to clearly and effectively communicate to executive board stakeholders.
Proficiency in utilising various reporting tools to analyse data- such as Excel, Think-Cell, Power Bi or Tableau.
Additional Information
Enjoy 5 weeks annual leave for pursuing your passions outside of work.
Enjoy the flexibility of hybrid work options.
Support during life’s most important moments including paid parental leave, including superannuation on parental leave.
Complimentary access to free physiotherapy to treat non-work related aches, pains or niggles.
Work with a company who has been recognised as an Employer of Choice every year since 2018 - 2024.
Boost your wellbeing with the MyALDI wellbeing program with discounted access to Fitness Passport and health insurance.

Remuneration:

Transparent tiered salary range of $143,400 - $163,500 including Superannuation.

At ALDI, we celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. We welcome applications from people of all backgrounds, experiences, abilities, and identities. To learn more, please visit www.aldicareers.com.au

Job Description

Join a highly impactful team as a Strategy Analyst (Commercial) in the Financial Planning and Analysis (FP&A) department of ALDI Stores, based in Minchinbury. This is a 12-month contract opportunity. 

You will play a key role in driving financial strategies by providing clear commercial insight into how strategic initiatives and investments impact cost, profitability, and return on capital in a retail environment. You will have the opportunity to leave a lasting imprint on the business and influencing the business to maintain its competitive position in the market.

What does the role involve?   

Analyse and review market trends, key economic drivers of retail performance to connect strategies into operational activities and financial outcomes.
Review strategic initiatives and programs for financial logic, feasibility, impact and synthesise ambiguity into clear messages.
Support capital allocation and investment decisions through structured business cases and link operational performance to financial and RNOA outcomes.
Contribute to the development and review of commercial frameworks  and processes to optimise decision-making and operational effectiveness.
Translate complex datasets from multiple sources, financial models and develop board-ready presentations and documents.
Report and analyse actuals against budgets and forecasts, providing in-depth commercial insights into performance.

And the best part? Every single day at ALDI, you'll know you're making a difference, supporting our mission to help everyday Australians live richer lives for less.

Qualifications
Demonstrated experience within a commercial finance, consulting, business analysis environment or similar highly regarded.
Background in Big 4, strategy consulting, internal strategy, or PMO highly regarded.
Proven demonstrated experience of financial planning, analysis, developing business cases and assessing performance analysis.
Ability to leverage data-driven insights to inform and drive strategic decision-making within a dynamic business environment.
Exceptional communication skills with the ability to synthesis information to Executive Board stakeholders.
Proficiency in utilising various reporting tools to analyse data- such as Excel, Think-Cell, Power Bi or Tableau.

Process Improvement Specialist




Are you ready to make a real impact in Australia’s energy transition?




At AusNet, we play a key role in the energy transition and provide essential energy to Victorian households and businesses.




Help us lead the way, while enriching your career with real people who encourage you to bring your best and make real impact – for your career, our communities and Australia’s clean energy future.







About the role




The Process Improvement Specialist drives enterprise‑wide process excellence by facilitating stakeholder workshops, mapping processes from level 1 to 5, uncovering inefficiencies, and leading improvement initiatives that support safe, reliable, and efficient energy services. You will coach process owners and stewards to build capability and embed a culture of continuous improvement using Lean, Six Sigma, and Kaizen.


You will leverage business process management tools to model and mine processes, extract insights, and visualise real‑time flows to identify deviations, bottlenecks, and performance gaps, supporting workflow redesign, automation, and best‑practice implementation.


The role supports the enterprise process management framework by ensuring processes are mapped, well‑documented, version‑controlled, and accessible for training, audits, and ongoing improvement. By strengthening end‑to‑end processes and regulatory readiness, the Process Improvement Specialist helps embed operational excellence that drives performance, innovation, and resilience.







Key Responsibilities




Support the enterprise process framework and tools by driving implementation, adoption, and continuous improvement, ensuring processes are mapped, documented, optimised, and aligned with enterprise standards and best practices.

Facilitate cross‑functional workshops with frontline staff, SMEs, and leadership to map current‑state processes, identify pain points, co‑design future‑state improvements, and build process ownership across functions.

Lead enterprise‑wide improvement initiatives across Gas Operations, Electricity Distribution, Transmission, Digital, Future Networks, Group Operations and Corporate Functions to improve safety, efficiency, reliability, compliance, and customer service.

Conduct end‑to‑end diagnostics of operational and support processes to identify inefficiencies, waste, duplication, and bottlenecks using Lean, Six Sigma, and value stream mapping.

Standardise and document critical processes in line with AusNet’s Integrated Management System (IMS), regulatory requirements, and operational risk frameworks.

Partner with leaders and technical specialists to translate strategic objectives into operational workflows and continuous improvement initiatives that deliver measurable performance uplift.

Collaborate with Data & Analytics and Digital Enablement to develop dashboards, KPIs, and real‑time visualisation tools that support decision‑making and process monitoring.

Embed continuous improvement capability by coaching team leaders, field supervisors, and support staff in CI tools, root‑cause analysis, visual management, and standard work.

Support transformation and change programs, including process re‑engineering for new systems, organisational shifts, and major capital project delivery.

Ensure operational processes meet compliance obligations, including safety, environmental performance, regulator reporting (AER, ESV), and critical infrastructure risk management.

Capture lessons learned from incidents, audits, and emergency management exercises and integrate them into sustainable improvements and training materials.

Lead process maturity assessments across business units and contribute to the enterprise Operational Excellence maturity roadmap and reporting cadence.

Drive cross‑business process harmonisation by identifying and resolving variation that impacts performance, regulatory alignment, or scalability across regulated networks and Future Networks developments. 







What You’ll Bring

You bring advanced facilitation and workshop leadership skills, engaging stakeholders from field teams to executives. You have strong process mapping, problem‑solving, and analytical skills using BPM tools, Confluence, or similar.




You coach others in CI tools, build local capability, and communicate complex process issues clearly. You are proficient in root cause analysis, standard work design, and process documentation, and you manage multiple initiatives concurrently while delivering outcomes in fast‑paced or ambiguous environments.




 

Qualifications:

Tertiary qualification in Engineering, Operations Management, Business, or a related discipline.

Certified in Lean Six Sigma (minimum Green Belt required; Black Belt desirable).

Formal training in continuous improvement, change management, or operational excellence methodologies (e.g. Kaizen, A3 thinking, root cause analysis).

Familiarity with ISO standards and integrated management systems (e.g. ISO 9001, ISO 55001) is advantageous.







 

Skills:

5+ years' experience in process improvement and operational excellence.

Skilled in facilitating cross-functional workshops to map current state, co-design future state, and foster ownership. 

Experienced in coaching individuals and teams on process management and continuous improvement.

Demonstrated experience leading end-to-end improvement projects with measurable business outcomes.

Proven track record in embedding sustainable process change and building capability at team level.

Strong understanding of continuous improvement methodologies such as Lean, Six Sigma, Kaizen, and value stream mapping.

Knowledge of operational processes within asset-intensive, safety-critical, or regulated environments (e.g. energy, utilities, infrastructure).

Familiarity with integrated management systems (IMS), ISO standards (e.g. ISO 9001, ISO 55001), and regulatory compliance frameworks.

Awareness of key business functions including field operations, emergency management, asset management, safety, and capital delivery.







Please note, we will not be engaging in Recruitment agencies for this role, please apply directly!

 

 

 

A real place to belong.




We celebrate unique voices, refreshing perspectives and diversity in our team. Engage and connect through our social club, wide range of events or by joining one of our Employee Network Groups.




We believe in more than just competitive pay. Here’s what sets us apart:

Leave: more than typical personal leave and a generous 14 weeks of paid parental leave, with no minimum service.

Community giving: a paid day to volunteer with our social impact partner, Foodbank, or for a cause that matters to you.

Perks: we offer all the other perks you’ve come to expect like purchased leave, income protection insurance, novated leasing, corporate discounts, private health cover discounts and more.




As an industry in transformation, we’re excited by the possibilities ahead.

So, if you’re passionate about our purpose and committed to making real progress, bring your energy and join AusNet. Together, we can shape a new way forward.

Ad Text:
6 months max term fulltime opportunity (with view to extend)
Located at Norwest offering hybrid work arrangements
Be part of a supportive team delivering impactful technology solutions

About the Role:

As a Business Analyst, you will work with stakeholders from all parts of BaptistCare to elicit requirements and capture business needs, to articulate and document business requirements, to conduct as-is/to-be business process mapping and business process design, to participate in project delivery through design reviews and walk-throughs, to validate and communicate outcomes.

Step into a high-impact role at the heart of a major acquisition. As our Business Analyst, you’ll play a pivotal role in transitioning and integrating the acquisition of 10 Retirement Villages into our broader WA operations. You’ll lead the charge in consolidating and migrating critical data, ensuring a smooth, well-orchestrated transition from day one.

You’ll dive deep into end-to-end business processes; from sales, bonds and admissions through to payroll, accounts payable, onboarding and aged debtors—capturing the workflows, system processes and business rules that keep operations running.

By comparing incumbent processes with BaptistCare’s ways of working, you’ll uncover gaps, overlaps and opportunities for improvement, helping shape a stronger, more streamlined future state. You’ll also be central to migration planning, bringing clarity to priorities, sequencing and dependencies to keep this complex transition on track.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead the documentation of current-state business processes associated with the data entry onto systems, document the integrations, data flows and storage locations.
Map end-to-end workflows and system processes, capturing key business rules and operational dependencies.
lead a comparison analysis of processes and data to identify gaps, overlaps and improvement opportunities in Baptistcare’s systems.
Define the migration approach to BaptistCare’s core systems, including but not limited to Epicor, TechOne, MS Dynamics, Salesforce).
Identify and prioritise capability uplift and system enhancements to support the acquisition and future-state design.
Support transition planning by clarifying priorities, sequencing and dependencies to ensure a smooth integration.

About the Team:

The Information & Digital team drives innovation and transforms care at BaptistCare through cutting-edge technology, seamless operations, and smart risk management. You’ll join a collaborative, solutions-focused team that values creativity, flexibility, and turning complex projects into real-world impact for our frontline teams..

About You:

Minimum 5 years’ experience as a business analyst delivering complex process, data and system change initiatives.
Demonstrated experience working on enterprise system implementations or replacements, particularly finance, payroll, CRM or care-related platforms.
Tertiary qualification in Business, Information Technology, Business Analysis or a related discipline.
Experience in mapping, analysing, and improving business processes using BPMN or other structured process methodologies.
Solid understanding of systems, data and integration concepts, with the ability to document application and data architectures.
Experience defining and supporting data and system migration approaches, including sequencing, dependencies and risk considerations.
High-level written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate complex concepts for executives, business users and technical team
Previous experience participating on Project teams
Experience using business analysis and delivery tools such as Visio, Jira, Confluence, MS Project or equivalent.
Ability to develop relationships with key organisational stakeholders, including Execs and Business users.
Highly developed interpersonal skills and ability to work harmoniously in a team environment.

Desirable experience includes:

Experience in acquisitions, transitions or large-scale migrations, ideally involving multi-system environments, highly desirable
Experience with Healthcare and Aged Care systems and technology

Join us on our mission to make a better world of work. 

Culture Amp is the world’s leading employee experience platform, revolutionizing how 25 million employees across more than 6,500 companies create a better world of work. Culture Amp empowers companies of all sizes and industries to transform employee engagement, drive performance management, and develop high-performing teams. Powered by people science and the most comprehensive employee dataset in the world, the most innovative companies including Canva, On, Asana, Dolby, McDonalds and Nasdaq depend on Culture Amp every day.

Culture Amp is backed by leading venture capital funds and has offices in the US, UK, Germany and Australia. Culture Amp has been recognized as one of the world’s top private cloud companies by Forbes and most innovative companies by Fast Company.

For more information visit cultureamp.com.

How you can help make a better world of work

We're looking for a Senior Engineer to join the AI Research & Experience team, helping build AI Coach - Culture Amp's contextually-aware AI system that integrates survey insights, performance management, and interpersonal dynamics to deliver personalized support to organizations, teams, and individuals at scale.

You'll work at the intersection of applied AI research and product engineering, translating cutting-edge techniques into production systems that genuinely improve how people experience work. This isn't a research lab - you'll be shipping features that solve real customer problems. 

What you'll do

Staying up to date with current research, literature and provider offerings. 
Design, implement and evaluate areas and features of our multi-agentic platform and systems using modern frameworks (e.g., LangGraph) for stateful, multi-turn coaching conversations.
Advise, help build, and orchestrate data pipelines that unify fragmented workplace data (surveys, goals, performance reviews, feedback, 1-1 notes) into coherent coaching context
Translate customer requirements into technical solutions - working backwards from user needs to system design. Creating technical documentation to support literacy, technical transfer and engineering practice.
Partner closely with product, design, and people science to ensure the features developed are fit for purpose, and in-line with the existing product expectations to ensure seamless partnership transfer of technology.
Contribute to evaluation frameworks and bias testing to meet enterprise requirements for transparency and fairness
Build cutting-edge, working prototypes, integrated into our environments which validate new approaches and accelerate learning.
What we're looking for


Must Haves:

Proven commercial experience taking ML/AI systems to production.
Strong technical writer and communicator
Full stack software development experience, ideally Python, React, PGVector
Strong software engineering fundamentals - you write clean, tested, maintainable code. 
You leverage Software development AI tooling effectively.
Experience with LLM application development (prompt and context engineering, RAG, agent architectures)
Hands-on experience designing and integrating data pipelines - you're comfortable moving data across systems, working within rigorous security standards, handling messy real-world inputs, and building robust orchestration
A pragmatic, solution-focused mindset - you evaluate new technology through the lens of "does this scalably solve the problem?" not "is this technically interesting?"
You fit our values with the proactivity to take risks, and the humility to learn in public. You take pride in your work and its successful utilisation, stability, extendability and maintainability. 

Strong signals:

Experience at startups or founding teams - comfortable with ambiguity and fast iteration
Postgraduate degree (Masters or PhD) in Machine Learning, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, or related quantitative field
Evidence of taking cutting-edge (relevant) techniques from paper to production
Experience with evaluation/benchmarking frameworks for AI systems
Experience integrating scalable solutions such as advanced Speech-to-Text (STT) and Text-to-Speech (TTS) pipelines (e.g., Whisper, ElevenLabs) with streaming capabilities
Experience implementing GraphRAG or Knowledge Graphs (e.g., Neo4j)

Bonus:

Familiarity with people analytics, HR tech, or behavioral science applications
Contributions to data ethics, algorithmic fairness, or responsible AI initiatives
Open source contributions or public technical writing
Why join AIRX


You'll work at scale on hard problems that matter - building AI that helps organizations develop their people, improve feedback culture, and foster the conditions for sustainable high performance. Our approach is deeply informed by Culture Amp's people science research. You'll be surrounded by talented and passionate advocates for humanity and cutting edge AI in the world of work.

We believe that our employees are the heartbeat of our success. We're committed to fostering a work environment that truly cares for and develops its people, and creates lasting positive impact. In addition to providing a competitive compensation package, some of the key benefits we offer are: 

Employee Share Options Program: We empower you to be an owner in Culture Amp and share in our success
Programs, coaching, and budgets to help you thrive personally and professionally
Access to external providers for mental wellbeing and coaching support to sustain the wellbeing, safety and development of our people
Monthly Camper Life Allowance: An automatic allowance paid out each month with your pay - you can spend it however you like to help improve your experience and life outside work
Team budgets dedicated to team building activities and connection
Intentional quarterly wellbeing pauses: A quarterly company-wide shutdown day in each region to to collectively pause, reset and focus on restoration and rest, without having to tap into individual vacation time
Extended year-end breaks: An extended refresh period at the end of year
Excellent parental leave and in work support program available from day 1 of joining Culture Amp
5 Social Impact Days a year to make a positive impact on the community outside of work
MacBooks for you to do your best & a work from home office budget to spend on setting up your home office
Medical insurance coverage for you and your family (Available for US & UK only) 

Additionally, we don't just focus on our internal community; we believe in creating a better world of work for all. We're committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion, with Employee Resource Groups and ally communities in place. 

We have a strong commitment to Anti-Racism, and endeavor to lead by example. Every step we make as a business towards anti-racism is another step we can take to support our customers in making a better world (of work). You can see our current commitments to Anti-Racism here.

Salary: Not for Profit Salary Packaging on offer
Ad Text:
2 years max term fulltime opportunity (with view to extend)
Flexible location across NSW, WA, VIC and TAS, with the option to work in a hybrid model
Contribute to high‑quality project delivery across a diverse and growing organisation

About the Role:

As a Business Analyst, you will work with stakeholders from all parts of BaptistCare to elicit requirements and capture business needs, to articulate and document business requirements, to conduct as-is/to-be business process mapping and business process design, to participate in project delivery through design reviews and walk-throughs, to validate and communicate outcomes.

You’ll play a pivotal role in transforming aged care through technology by supporting the selection and rollout of our new national clinical records platform across all 51 aged care homes. You’ll assess existing clinical systems, conduct market scans for alternative solutions, and evaluate applications to identify the best platform for BaptistCare. Beyond selection, you’ll be instrumental in supporting the implementation of the chosen solution, ensuring smooth integration into daily operations and delivering tangible benefits for both residents and staff. This is a unique opportunity to apply your analytical expertise, process insight, and passion for improving clinical care through innovative technology.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead structured analysis and documentation to support the selection and implementation of a national clinical records platform, reducing the risk of vendor or configuration issues.
Facilitate stakeholder engagement, capturing clinical and operational requirements, workflows, and concerns to ensure all perspectives are reflected in evaluation and design decisions.
Conduct detailed gap analysis of current clinical systems to define must-have features, ensuring the new solution meets both operational and clinical needs.
Develop evaluation criteria and assessment metrics, providing objective, transparent comparison of vendor solutions.
Analyse and document all cost components, highlighting variances and providing insights to support informed financial decision-making.
Support transition and implementation planning, clarifying priorities, sequencing, and dependencies to ensure smooth adoption across all 51 aged care homes.
Translate complex processes and data into clear, actionable insights to guide strategic decisions and optimise clinical operations.

About the Team:

The Information & Digital team drives innovation and transforms care at BaptistCare through cutting-edge technology, seamless operations, and smart risk management. You’ll join a collaborative, solutions-focused team that values creativity, flexibility, and turning complex projects into real-world impact for our frontline teams.

About You:

Minimum 5 years’ experience as a business analyst delivering complex process, data and system change initiatives.
Previous experience within healthcare and/or aged care sector or consultancy experience
Demonstrated experience working on enterprise system implementations or replacements, particularly clinical systems e.g.: (EHR, EMR solutions).
Tertiary qualification in Business, Information Technology, Business Analysis or a related discipline.
Experience in mapping, analysing, and improving business processes using BPMN or other structured process methodologies.
Solid understanding of systems, data and integration concepts, with the ability to document application and data architectures.
Experience defining and supporting data and system migration approaches, including sequencing, dependencies and risk considerations.
High-level written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate complex concepts for executives, business users and technical team
Previous experience participating on Project teams
Experience using business analysis and delivery tools such as Visio, Jira, Confluence, MS Project or equivalent.
Ability to develop relationships with key organisational stakeholders, including Execs and Business users.
Highly developed interpersonal skills and ability to work harmoniously in a team environment.

Passionate about creating impactful solutions that support those we serve? We’d love to hear from you!

About Us:

We are proud to be part of the merged care organisation that will be known nationally as BaptistCare. As a for purpose, Christian care organisation, we are committed to providing exceptional support and services across Australia.  Together with Baptcare (VIC, TAS, SA) and Baptist Care SA we employ over 12,000 dedicated employees and support over 38,000 customers to help people live well with dignity and purpose. From older Australians and their families to people facing significant disadvantage, our passion and our priority are the customers we serve. We strive to deliver care as it should be – with people right at the centre. 

We love what we do and the communities we help. With us you can deliver life transforming care, create a career you’ll love, and join a team who make a difference.

Location: Orange, Blue Mountains & Central West NSW
Ad Text:
Company description:



Workplace Type: Onsite

About Newmont


At Newmont, we're not just a world-leading gold and metals producer - we're a team united by our commitment to shaping a more inclusive, sustainable, and responsible mining industry. Joining us means becoming part of a global, diverse workforce where everyone is valued, empowered, and encouraged to grow. Our people are the heart of our success, bringing exceptional skill, integrity, and dedication to everything we do as an organization and we're dedicated to creating a workplace where everyone can thrive.

About Cadia


Our Cadia Valley Operation in New South Wales is situated about 25 kilometers from Orange and 250 kilometers west of Sydney. Cadia produces gold doré bars from a gravity circuit and gold-rich copper concentrates from a flotation circuit. The operation includes the Cadia East Mine which is globally renowned for its use of block caving, a large-scale underground mining method.


We acknowledge the Wiradjuri people, traditional custodians of the land surrounding Cadia, and proudly run an Indigenous Buddy Program to enrich the workplace experience our Indigenous employees. As a residential (drive-in / drive-out) mine, Cadia values community deeply, offering both financial and in-kind support to organizations across Blayney, Cabonne, and Orange townships. The Orange region is often referred to as the gateway to Country New South Wales with acclaimed wineries, fine dining, annual festivals and charming heritage villages making for an unparalleled work-life balance.

Who we're looking for

We are seeking an experienced Analyst Asset Management to play a critical role in driving cost discipline, financial transparency and reliability outcomes across our fixed plant operations. We value transferable skills and diverse backgrounds — if this role excites you, we'd love to talk.

This is a senior individual contributor role suited to someone who thrives at the intersection of engineering, financial modelling and enterprise systems—delivering accurate budgets, robust forecasts and data-driven insights that improve asset and maintenance strategies.

About the Role

Reporting to the Supervisor, you will support significant fixed-plant OPEX and CAPEX portfolios, partnering closely with Asset Management, Planning & Scheduling, Finance and site leadership.

Your work will anchor the site's cost performance through budget development, cost analytics, strategy economics, BI reporting and high-quality data governance across SAP and our work management systems.

You will grow the strategic and financial skillset of an Asset Manager while remaining an individual contributor.

Key Responsibilities:

Build and maintain detailed OPEX and CAPEX budgets and forecasts at equipment and strategy level
Deliver monthly plan-vs-actual reporting, variance analysis and unit-cost insights
Analyse key cost drivers including materials, labour, contractors and downtime, and track savings initiatives
Translate engineering analysis outcomes into financially quantified maintenance strategy improvements (NPV/IRR)
Design and maintain Power BI dashboards integrating work order, vendor, materials and budget and actuals cost data
Ensure strong SAP S/4HANA, FieldGlass and MOS/WMS data hygiene and contractor cost reconciliation
Support outage and preventative maintenance planning through accurate cost and materials alignment
Coach planners and supervisors on financial discipline, data quality and continuous improvement practices
Prepare management packs and facilitate regular cost and performance reviews with senior stakeholders

You are analytical, commercially minded and confident operating in complex operational environments. You enjoy working with large datasets, challenging assumptions and influencing decisions through clear, evidence‑based insights.

You will bring:

Tertiary qualifications in Engineering, Finance, Economics or Commerce are valued, however, we also welcome applicants from trade or maintenance backgrounds who have built strong CMMS capability, analytical skills and commercial acumen through experience and further study.
Strong experience in asset-intensive or fixed-plant environments, ideally within maintenance or reliability.
Demonstrated capability in budgeting, forecasting and cost modelling for large operations
Advanced CMMS literacy (SAP skills highly regarded), with strong Power BI and Excel skills
Experience applying strategy economics, PMO/Criticality and risk-based maintenance principles
The ability to coach and influence cross-functional stakeholders to deliver initiatives and uplift cost control and data quality improvements.
A proactive, improvement-focused mindset aligned to safety, compliance and operational excellence

Please note this is a residential role in Orange, NSW with a 5/2 (Monday to Friday) or 5/2-4/3 (9 day fortnight) work pattern.



Job description:

Unique opportunity with the Asset Management team at Cadia

Contract | Immediate Start | Adelaide (Hybrid)

An enterprise scale transformation program is underway to modernise and integrate clinical, ancillary medical and enterprise systems within a complex healthcare environment. We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to play a pivotal role within the Clinical & Ancillary workstream of this major technology transition.

This role will suit an experienced Business Analyst who is confident operating in hospital or healthcare settings and enjoys working across both business and technical teams to deliver fit-for-purpose clinical and operational solutions.

Key responsibilities include:

Leading requirements elicitation, documentation and validation across clinical, patient administration and ancillary medical systems
Analysing current-state processes and identifying opportunities for improvement and standardisation
Supporting fit-gap analysis with vendor solutions and documenting functional specifications
Working with technical teams on integration, reporting and data migration requirements
Contributing to change impact assessments, training inputs and adoption activities
Supporting UAT planning, test case development and issue resolution
Maintaining clear traceability across requirements, design decisions and deliverables
You will bring:

5+ years’ experience as a Business Analyst within large, complex environments (healthcare or hospital experience strongly preferred)
Strong understanding of clinical, patient administration and broader enterprise processes (finance, HR, procurement)
Proven experience with requirements management, fit-gap analysis and functional documentation
Confidence engaging with a wide range of stakeholders, from clinicians and operational teams through to senior leaders
Exposure to vendor-led enterprise or clinical systems (e.g. ERP, PAS, medical or hospital platforms)
Excellent communication, facilitation and analytical skills
The ability to work autonomously within a structured program environment
Engagement Details
Contract role aligned to a major transformation workstream
Immediate start available
Hybrid working arrangement (4 days onsite, 1 day remote)
Adelaide-based

Ad Text:
Hybrid work environment
Based at our Sydney CBD Head Office
Play an important part shaping the future of our iconic Australian institution

We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst to join the Payment Operations Program (POP) Project on a 12‑month fixed-term salaried contract.

In this role, you will be responsible for delivering high‑quality foundational gap analysis and developing effective remediation solutions to support the project's objectives.

Success in this position will require advanced communication skills and exceptional stakeholder management, supported by demonstrated experience in a similar role engaging a broad, horizontally diverse cross‑section of the bank at an enterprise level.

Your background

Deep expertise in delivering business analysis for large scale complex data migration projects.
Exceptional interpersonal skills to collaborate, influence and partner effectively with key business and technical stakeholders across the Reserve Bank.
Strong business analysis experience, knowledge and skillsets.
Experienced in understanding, gathering, and documenting complex requirements for a variety of business areas, systems and domains.
Proven track record of successful end to end project delivery experience (Agile/Waterfall) in large enterprise environments, with a focus on meeting deadlines and achieving objectives.
An energetic and strategic thinker who has a meticulous attention to detail.
Fast learner with a curious and proactive mindset-willing to drive progress and delivery proactively.


Additional requirements

Strong working knowledge of ITIL v4 frameworks and practices
Demonstrated experience in Agile and hybrid Agile/Waterfall environments, including writing user stories, acceptance criteria, and process documentation
Proficiency in process mapping and producing high-quality documentation such as service definitions, process flows, and RACI matrices
Solid understanding of system integrations and external interfaces
Strong capability to analyse data, identify key insights, and interpret their potential implications
Demonstrated capability to engage and influence enterprise‑level stakeholders through clear, credible verbal and written communication


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.


Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people.

Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go.

Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts.

We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

About us: 
Unitywater operates in one of Australia’s most exceptional environments in terms of natural beauty, geographical and demographic breadth. We operate on Kabi Kabi, Jinibara and Turrbal Country, proudly providing safe and reliable water to customers in Moreton Bay, Sunshine Coast and Noosa. We are a water utility serving one of the fastest growing regions in the country. 
We think a pretty good job starts here. 
  
About the role: 
At Unitywater, we’re shaping the future of water and wastewater services for our community and we’re looking for a Planning and Analysis Manager to help us do it.
In this pivotal role, you’ll lead and inspire a high-performing team, empowering the business with insights that matter. You’ll partner closely with senior leaders across the organisation, providing forward-looking financial planning, forecasting and analysis that directly drives business performance and investment decisions.
Your work will be at the centre of linking people, performance and strategy, making a meaningful difference to Unitywater, our customers, and our community.

As our Planning and Analysis Manager, you will:

Partner with leaders to deliver data-driven, forward-thinking insights.
Lead business unit planning including rolling forecasts, budgeting and long-range modelling.
Drive performance reporting that empowers decision-making at every level.
Inspire and grow your team to build capability and deliver impactful analysis and advice.
Champion innovation in reporting and analytics, driving automation, self-service and digital capability.
Strengthen investment governance with financial modelling and scenario planning.[SW1]
This role is more than numbers, it’s about shaping Unitywater’s strategic future, influencing decisions at the highest level, and building a culture of insight and performance.
This is your opportunity to influence, build a culture of insight and performance, and help shape a sustainable future with Unitywater. If you’re a collaborative, future-focused leader ready to make an impact, we’d love to hear from you.
  
About you: 
Our One Unitywater behaviours - Create the Future, Care Together, and Own It – define how we work together at Unitywater. To contribute to this, you will demonstrate the following skills and qualities for the role: The requirements for the position are:

Professional expertise: CA/CPA qualified with strong foundations in finance, planning and performance.

​Full time, continuing position with the University of Sydney as a Senior Clarity Analyst to drive strategic decision-making by providing critical insights and recommendations based on comprehensive data analysis, ensuring the University's projects are aligned with its strategic objectives

About the opportunity

The Strategic Program Office is pivotal in executing the Sydney in 2032 strategy, contributing to our vision of becoming "a better place to work, and a place that works better." Significant strategic initiatives are already in progress and as we enter the third year of strategy implementation, the University must continue to successfully deliver numerous initiatives, programs, and projects to achieve our 2032 goals.

The Senior Clarity Analyst is responsible for the end-to-end functional design, configuration and development, uplift, user experience, training and reporting processes for the Clarity system. Thus, providing critical insights into portfolio performance through a well-configured and fit-for-purpose Clarity platform. The role further involves collecting, analysing, and synthesising data from portfolio projects to create comprehensive reports and dashboards for university stakeholders. In addition to supporting the Head of Program Insights, they take a proactive role in enhancing reporting capabilities through hands-on configuration and development within Clarity, implementing advanced analytical techniques, optimising reporting processes, and ensuring data accuracy and consistency across the portfolio. This role collaborates across the Strategic Program Office and broader Strategy portfolio to translate business and reporting requirements into Clarity functional requirements and technical solution design, including configuration and development, monitor KPIs, and provide recommendations for improving portfolio management reporting. The role also contributes to the continuous improvement of the portfolio performance data management and reporting framework.

The Senior Clarity Analyst plays a crucial support role by ensuring the Clarity system is fit for purpose, is actively configured and evolved to incorporate new parameters and functionality and seeks to benefit from other Clarity blueprints and templates across the University.

Through their analytical skills and attention to detail, they help deliver reliable and consistent project information, laying the groundwork for effective project governance and control. Their ability to optimise reporting processes and communicate complex data insights makes them an essential resource for the Strategic Program Office.

Your key responsibilities will be to:

own the configuration, development and continuous improvement of the Clarity system
support the Head of Program Insights in aligning reporting outputs with strategic University objectives
ensure Clarity can support in-depth data analysis through appropriate configuration of objects, attributes, workflows and reporting structures to identify patterns, trends, and potential risks across the portfolio
assess, design and implement Clarity configuration changes associated with new functionality releases, including impact assessment, regression considerations and stakeholder communication
provide high-level data analysis and interpretation, transforming complex data sets into meaningful insights and actionable recommendations
ensure clear and concise reporting that facilitates understanding and decision-making at all levels of the organisation
develop training materials and deliver training sessions for Clarity users, and lead discussions with stakeholders to explore ways to enhance performance reporting and achieve strategic outcomes.

About you:

demonstrated hands-on experience configuring and developing with Broadcom Clarity PPM, including objects, attributes, workflows, financials and reporting
bachelor's degree and/or an equivalent combination of training and experience
demonstrated experience in applying and advising on portfolio and investment management practices, supported by methodologies such asPrince2, P3M3, PMBok or equivalent
experience in designing and implementing whole-of-organisation processes that are consultative and encourage support and buy-in from diverse stakeholders
experience in stakeholder engagement with broad and diverse groups resulting in valuable stakeholder input
the ability to develop/cultivate productive relationships with internal and external stakeholders at all levels
working understanding and current knowledge of relevant aspects of the Work Health and Safety Policy and relevant legislation (including Safe Laboratory Practices for roles based in Laboratory).

a University contribution of 17% of your base salary to your superannuation fund
tax-efficient salary packaging options for cars, laptops, and additional contributions to your superannuation fund
generous relocation allowance if moving from interstate or overseas
access to fitness passport, as well as discounted rates on university sports and fitness centre's

About the role

As the Manager, Quantitative Modelling, you will act as the organisation’s subject matter expert for Credit Risk Stress Testing and Collective Provisioning across all BOQ Group credit portfolios. You will oversee the monitoring, reporting and interpretation of collective provisioning model outcomes, providing meaningful insights that help inform decision‑making and strengthen the Group’s overall credit risk management framework.

In this role, you will lead the delivery, maintenance and enhancement of stress testing frameworks and methodologies across credit portfolios, including the uplift of capabilities aligned to BOQ’s transition to the Internal Ratings Based (IRB) approach. You will also drive the development of innovative stress testing methodologies for emerging and evolving risk types, such as Climate Risk, ensuring the organisation maintains a forward‑looking and resilient approach to risk measurement.

As a key stakeholder across the business, you will work closely with internal teams during regulatory and ICAAP stress testing cycles, ensuring timely responses to regulatory changes and audit findings. Your ability to identify and address data quality issues will be essential to maintaining the accuracy and reliability of BOQ’s quantitative models while supporting the organisation’s broader regulatory and strategic priorities.

About you




You bring 5–8 years of experience in a similar quantitative, analytical or credit risk role, supported by strong mathematical and statistical knowledge and a postgraduate qualification in a technical discipline. You have hands‑on experience in building and interpreting mathematical or statistical models, with exposure to Credit Risk, Collective Provisions, Stress Testing, Forecasting or Capital Reporting. Your understanding of how technical modelling activities connect to broader business outcomes enables you to communicate insights clearly and influence decision‑making across diverse stakeholders.

You are confident working with relevant programming languages such as SQL, SAS, VBA, R, Python or Databricks, and you’re familiar with version control tools including Git, Bitbucket or DevOps. Your background in financial services positions you well to navigate IFRS 9, Basel frameworks and APRA prudential standards, with any direct experience in these areas considered highly desirable. Alongside your technical capability, you bring strong stakeholder engagement and project management skills, allowing you to collaborate effectively and contribute to continuous improvement within a complex risk environment.

About us

BOQ Group is a truly unique group of challenger brands with a purpose – to provide a genuine alternative to Australian financial services for customers and employees.

Our family of brands (Bank of Queensland (BOQ), ME Bank, Virgin Money Australia, BOQ Specialist), each come with their own defined customer audience and brand personality, but share one goal – to build social capital through banking. That’s creating trust with customers, exploring staff potential and believing that tiny gestures and big ideas can change the world for communities.

BOQ Group’s inclusive vision is to foster a workspace that values and leverages difference and creates new possibilities, a place where our people feel confident to bring their best selves to work every day. We embrace difference and believe that our workforce should reflect the customers and communities that we serve.

Since 2021, BOQ Group is recognised as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA).

In 2023, we successfully implemented an innovative Reconciliation Plan, driving positive change and promoting inclusivity across BOQ Group.

Company description:



At ENGIE, great adventures always start with a simple "hello" and the desire to take action for tomorrow. If, like us, you strongly believe the energy transition holds opportunities for you and for everyone, then look no further — you belong with us!
Our goal is to be the best energy transition utility, and we have an ambition to reach net zero emissions by 2045. In Australia, this includes flexible power generation, energy retail services for homes and businesses, advanced energy management solutions, and a growing portfolio of future‑focused projects — from hydrogen and battery storage to wind and solar developments.



Job description:



ENGIE's Consumer Retail energy business is seeking a Senior Finance Business Partner with strong energy sector experience and deep capability in gross margin analysis, financial modelling and commercial insight. This is a fixed‑term opportunity until end of January 2027 suited to an experienced individual contributor (non‑manager) who enjoys complex analysis and partnering directly with business leaders.

About the Role

You will provide strategic financial support to leaders across our Consumer Retail energy portfolio, delivering insights that influence commercial decision‑making, strengthen financial governance, and drive operational and financial performance. This role requires someone who can translate complex data into clear, actionable guidance while maintaining strong control disciplines.

Key Responsibilities

Deliver strategic financial insights, commercial analysis and recommendations to support decision‑making across the Consumer Retail energy business.
Lead forecasting, budgeting, profitability and gross margin analysis, including customer and segment performance.
Prepare accurate, timely financial reporting, manage variance analysis and present insights to senior stakeholders.
Support month‑end close, strengthen internal controls and ensure compliance with financial and regulatory requirements.
Drive improvements across financial processes, systems, modelling and reporting frameworks.
Partner with commercial, product and operational teams to evaluate business cases, assess risks and influence strategic initiatives.

About You

Qualifications

Degree in Finance, Commerce or related field.
CA / CPA / CFA qualified.

Skills & Experience

Proven experience in Finance Business Partnering, ideally within the retail energy industry.
Strong understanding of gross margin, customer profitability, and integrated financial analysis (P&L, balance sheet, cash flow).
Highly developed analytical and modelling skills with the ability to interpret complex data.
Strong communication skills with experience presenting insights to senior leaders.
Advanced Excel capability and experience with forecasting/planning tools.
High attention to detail and a proactive, improvement-focused mindset.

Job Title: Principal Business Analyst (AI and Data Science Platform Delivery)
Ad Text:
We are looking for a Principal Business Analyst to join a platform function supporting AI and machine learning delivery across a large enterprise environment. This role is ideal for a senior BA who thrives in ambiguity, understands how Data Science delivery differs from traditional deterministic technology delivery, and can bridge business needs with platform execution across Product, Engineering, and Data teams. You will work closely with stakeholders to shape high impact AI use cases, translate complex requirements into structured delivery pathways, and enable scalable adoption of Data Science capabilities across the organisation.
Key Responsibilities
Engage stakeholders across business and technical teams to define and structure complex AI and analytics use cases
Translate ambiguous business problems into clear hypotheses, requirements, and delivery roadmaps
Partner with Data Science teams to support iterative model development, experimentation, and solution delivery
Work closely with Engineering and Product teams to ensure platform alignment and scalable execution
Develop high quality documentation including user stories, functional specifications, process flows, and operating model artefacts
Support governance, prioritisation, and stakeholder alignment across AI and platform initiatives
Drive business readiness, adoption, and value realisation for AI enabled capabilities
Skills and Experience
8 to 12+ years experience as a senior or principal Business Analyst, ideally within analytics, AI, or Data Science environments
Proven ability to operate in non deterministic ML delivery contexts where outcomes evolve through iteration
Strong stakeholder engagement skills across Product, Engineering, Data Science, and senior business leaders
Experience supporting platform or product led delivery models within complex organisations
Excellent structured problem solving, documentation, and communication capability
Experience within large scale enterprise analytics or retail environments highly regarded

Sydney (1-2 days in the CBD office)

Job Title: Principal Program Manager (AI and Data Science Platform Delivery)
Ad Text:
We are seeking a Principal Program Manager to lead strategic delivery at the intersection of Data Science, Product, and Engineering within a high performing enterprise AI and analytics environment. This role will focus on enabling scalable execution of AI and machine learning initiatives across complex organisations. You will play a key role in bridging the gap between Data Science teams working in iterative, non deterministic delivery cycles and engineering teams operating within more traditional delivery models. This is a senior, outcomes driven position requiring strong delivery discipline, executive stakeholder influence, and the ability to translate ambiguity into structured programs of work.

Key Responsibilities
Lead end to end delivery of complex AI, ML, and data platform initiatives across multiple squads and business units
Partner closely with Data Science, Engineering, and Product leaders to align priorities, roadmaps, and execution plans
Translate ambiguous business challenges into structured hypotheses, delivery workstreams, and measurable success metrics
Drive delivery in experimental ML environments where outcomes require test and learn approaches and iteration
Establish strong governance including delivery cadence, reporting, risk management, dependency planning, and decision forums
Ensure AI initiatives are operationalised effectively into enterprise platforms, workflows, and engineering systems
Manage senior stakeholder engagement across technical and business functions, ensuring alignment and adoption
Support scalable operating models that enable multiple Data Science teams to deliver consistently across the organisation
Skills and Experience
10+ years experience leading complex programs within AI, Data Science, advanced analytics, or platform delivery environments
Proven ability to operate across Data Science, Engineering, and Product teams in large scale organisations
Strong understanding of non deterministic ML delivery, including experimentation cycles, iteration, and operationalisation
Demonstrated ability to translate business problems into structured delivery programs and measurable value outcomes
Exceptional stakeholder management skills, able to influence at senior executive level
Strong governance and delivery discipline, with a hands on execution mindset
Experience in large enterprise analytics organisations, retail or similar environments highly regarded
Sydney (1-2 days in the CBD office)

Your New Role

Climate change is an essential part of AustralianSuper's ESG strategy and the Fund has made a commitment to achieve Net Zero carbon emissions by 2050 in our investment portfolio. This commitment builds on the actions AustralianSuper is currently taking to manage climate-related risks and opportunities in the Fund's portfolio and is consistent with AustralianSuper's objective of helping members achieve their best financial position in retirement.

As a result of the introduction of the Australian Sustainability Reporting Standards (ASRS), AustralianSuper's mandatory reporting requirements will significantly increase in the next two years. In addition, clearly articulating AustralianSuper's ESG strategy and ambitions in line with Australian standards is essential to bringing AustralianSuper's ESG agenda to life for Members and other stakeholders.

The Senior Analyst, Sustainability Reporting is a newly created role in the Reporting & Control team within the Finance domain, and will support the execution of AustralianSuper's existing and emerging ESG reporting obligations.

Key responsibilities will include;


Building processes and controls to enable AustralianSuper to meet existing and future ESG regulatory disclosure and reporting requirements;
Collaborating with colleagues across the Fund to gather data and contribute to the broader ESG reporting implementation project;
Validate, consolidate, enhance and analyse ESG data for both external and internal ESG reporting;
Providing information and insights to internal stakeholders and preparing responses to questions from external regulators related to ESG reporting; and
Working with the Fund's external auditor to support the audit and/or review of AustralianSuper's ESG reporting.






What You'll Need

Experience in an ESG related role with exposure to ESG strategy and framework development, transition to Net Zero, ESG due diligence, and sustainability reporting.
Strong written and oral communication skills with the ability to present ideas, perspectives and issues to management.
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills and the ability to work effectively with a range of people at all levels across an organisation and external stakeholders.
Significant experience in working under pressure, setting and manage conflicting priorities and meeting specified timeframes.
Comfortable with change and working in a multidisciplinary team across a global organisation.
Prior experience in translating ESG regulatory disclosure and reporting requirements and guidance into business processes and controls
Experience in sustainable finance and reporting with exposure to financial modelling and KPI (Key performance indicators) scorecards.
Passionate about sustainability and excited about the new challenges in ESG regulatory disclosure and reporting.
Tertiary qualifications in Accounting/ Finance/ Business and/or Engineering/ Environmental science/ Sustainability/ Governance or equivalent.
Completion of CA/CPA, or equivalent (desired).

About our Client
  
Our client is a specialist construction and field services organisation, delivering protective coating, asset maintenance and remediation services across large, asset-heavy environments.
  
The business operates across multiple core systems and is investing heavily in its data capability to move from fragmented reporting to a centralised, scalable analytics platform. As part of this journey is building a central Azure based data lake to support enterprise-wide reporting and core data insight.
  
About the Role   
  
This is a senior, hands-on Data Analyst role, working closely with a highly experienced Senior Data professional. 
  
The focus of the role is on data integration, ingestion and transformation, sitting between source systems and the Power BI reporting layer. This role is critical in designing and building the ETL pipelines and data flows that enable reliable, trusted reporting and overall strong architecture. 
  
The environment has limited documentation, so this role suits someone who is comfortable working hands-on, navigating ambiguity, and building strong data foundations from the ground up.
  
Key Responsibilities   

Build and maintain ETL / ELT pipelines from multiple operational systems into a central data lake.
Design and manage data integration and ingestion processes, including API-based integrations.
Develop clean, reliable and scalable datasets to support Power BI reporting.
Work closely with a Senior Data architect to align data flow, modelling and best-practice design.
Support and improve reporting from ERP and field service platforms (e.g. Jobpac / construction ERP systems).
Operate effectively in a low-documentation environment, taking ownership of data discovery and structure.
Key Requirements   

Proven experience in a Data Analyst or similar role within complex, operational environments.
Strong hands-on experience with ETL processes and data integration and Advanced SQL skills.
Solid experience with Power BI, including data modelling and semantic layer design.
Experience working with APIs and system integrations.
Strong understanding of data flow, data best practice and analytics enablement.
Ability to work closely with senior technical stakeholders and operate autonomously.
